lead_paragraph: Salah Abdeslam, wounded in a shootout with the Brussels police, is thought to be the last surviving member of the group that carried out deadly attacks on Paris in November.

byline.original: By AURELIEN BREEDEN and ALISSA J. RUBIN

headline.print_headline: Paris Suspect Claims He ‘Backed Out’ of Stadium Bombing, Prosecutor Says
headline.main: Paris Suspect Claims He ‘Backed Out’ of Stadium Bombing, Prosecutor Says

snippet: Salah Abdeslam, wounded in a shootout with the Brussels police, is thought to be the last surviving member of the group that carried out deadly attacks on Paris in November.
abstract: Suspected Paris terrorist attacker Salah Abdeslam tells French prosecutors he 'backed out' of detonating his suicide vest outside of Stade de France soccer stadium; authorities question reliability of attack's apparently last living suspect, who was captured in Brussels and has pledged to fight extradition to France.
